      "description": "Available is a concours-level 2008 Porsche 911 Carrera S (997.1), a definitive example of the marque's water-cooled evolution. Powered by the 3.8L M97.01 naturally aspirated flat-six, this unit features an optimized intake manifold and VarioCam Plus for a linear power band peaking at 355 hp. The 6-speed G97 manual transaxle provides crisp engagement, paired with a factory-optioned short-shift kit and Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) for variable damping control. Significant preventative maintenance has been executed, including an IMS bearing verification and a fresh rear main seal. The braking system utilizes four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing no signs of thermal stress. Zero cosmetic blemishes or mechanical deviations; this is a true turn-key investment for the discerning enthusiast.",
